[{"question":"And, Mark, it appears to me that the players are slowly starting to trickle back on the field, is that your assessment as you\u0027re looking?","answer":"Yes, the official -- the ball sits at the 40 yard line.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":54,"aSentId":55},{"question":"Do you like what you see for maybe the second term Obama already?","answer":"Oh, I love the man, I voted for him originally.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":83,"aSentId":84},{"question":"America needs to find other business models, doesn\u0027t it?","answer":"Well, it is.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":134,"aSentId":135},{"question":"Joe Carter?","answer":"Don, I can barely hear you, my man.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":224,"aSentId":225},{"question":"Ma\u0027am?","answer":"We\u0027ve got a school shooting.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":258,"aSentId":259},{"question":"What school?","answer":"Chardon High School.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":261,"aSentId":262},{"question":"UNIDENTIFIED 911 OPERATOR: Chardon High School?","answer":"Yes, ma\u0027am.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":263,"aSentId":264},{"question":"The moment that you were shot what goes through your mind?","answer":"What I -- what I really -- what was going through my mind was I had to get out of the high school and really nothing else flows through your mind.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":281,"aSentId":282},{"question":"How did you deal with it?","answer":"I had a lot of support.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":287,"aSentId":288},{"question":"Did you despair?","answer":"I mean, I did, yes.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":291,"aSentId":292},{"question":"Or what was it that they did that helped you?","answer":"Well, I had a lot of support from other people texting me and calling me that are in wheelchairs.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":298,"aSentId":299},{"question":"What was that like for you as his mother?","answer":".","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":319,"aSentId":320},{"question":"What is the prognosis they made?","answer":"They said that they were cautiously optimistic when they came out of surgery, but -- so we\u0027re still hoping and praying.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":332,"aSentId":333},{"question":"Very particular support group that knows exactly what you\u0027ve been through?","answer":"Well, if somebody who\u0027s been through it but has an outlook that\u0027s positive.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":341,"aSentId":342},{"question":"What do you think of that?","answer":"I would love that.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":358,"aSentId":359},{"question":"Shake on it?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":362,"aSentId":363},{"question":"Does that bring it all back?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":379,"aSentId":380},{"question":"But aside from that, have you set yourself things that you really want to achieve?","answer":"Well, obviously, I had to -- I had to switch around my career a little bit that I was aiming for.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":401,"aSentId":402},{"question":"What would you want to be?","answer":"I wanted to be just an electrician in the union and I don\u0027t believe that can happen practically right now.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":404,"aSentId":405},{"question":"Before you met Tony, what was -- what was your life like?","answer":"I was doing a lot of current therapies, you know, psychiatry, psychology, which I started in 2011.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":431,"aSentId":432},{"question":"Did it help, any of that?","answer":"Yes, yes.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":436,"aSentId":437},{"question":"So you had -- why don\u0027t you tell him what your symptoms were at the time?","answer":"Basically insomnia.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":439,"aSentId":440},{"question":"What was the rock bottom moment for you?","answer":"The rock bottom moment for me in a sense was -- it was after my second divorce, just being -- I pushed so many people away, couldn\u0027t figure out why I felt this way.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":445,"aSentId":446},{"question":"What do you say in this situation?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s interesting, and we\u0027ve done this with hundreds of wounded warriors and different soldiers.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":454,"aSentId":455},{"question":"What advice would you give him?","answer":"Well, basically, he has to take back his life.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":474,"aSentId":475},{"question":"He built a small business to start with and one of those young women that worked for him was addicted to meth, is that right?","answer":"Methamphetamine, right.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":530,"aSentId":531},{"question":"Why don\u0027t you share with him the story of how you end up in your new business?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":532,"aSentId":533},{"question":"What was that like for you?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":567,"aSentId":568},{"question":"Or do you have a little bit of (INAUDIBLE), which is that ferocity of spirit?","answer":"I think ferocity of spirit is critical for everybody, but we all have it.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":579,"aSentId":580},{"question":"ORGAN: Do we all have it?","answer":"Yes, we do.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":582,"aSentId":583},{"question":"Is that a good focus to look at children, to look at other things and say, \"You know what, stop feeling sorry for myself; it\u0027s for him, for her, it\u0027s for that\"?","answer":"Most of it -- I think what\u0027s really beautiful about most human beings is that we\u0027ll do more for others we love than we\u0027ll ever do for ourselves.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":624,"aSentId":625},{"question":"And Mike, what do you -- what do you say to these people suffering in America right now?","answer":"I got to tell you, Tony is absolutely right.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":635,"aSentId":636},{"question":"But actually all those emotions are just barriers to getting back on your feet, aren\u0027t they?","answer":"That\u0027s correct.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":654,"aSentId":655},{"question":"If I should (INAUDIBLE), you can have any one thing, you can have good health, you can have money, you can have the fame that allows you to inspire people, what would you choose as the one thing?","answer":"Certainly I think without health, you\u0027re not around to do anything.","docId":"130203pmt","qSentId":721,"aSentId":722}]